
TCP guarantees reliable communication through acknowledgements, retransmissions, and buffering out-of-order segments.

It also calculates the Retransmission Timeout (RTO) to determine when lost packets should be resent.

Cybersecurity Relevance

High retransmission rates can indicate network congestion, packet loss, denial-of-service attacks, or unstable Command-and-Control traffic.

Out-of-order packets may also be intentionally crafted to evade IDS inspection.

